# Mid-rewire benchmark warning window — ACTIVE

**Window opened:** commit `c3b989fad` (2026-04-24) — 2k.a
(`feat(wallet): 2k.a — rewire load/verify/rewrite onto SHKW1 handle`).

**Window closes:** commit that lands 2m-cache
(`docs/MID_REWIRE_HARDENING.md` §3.3.1). 2m-cache deletes the
last dual-stack path (`cache_file_data`, boost-serialize cache
blocks, inline atomic-write) and is the point at which the
benchmark baseline and the live code stop being structurally
asymmetric. Delete this file in the same commit as 2m-cache.

## What this file does

The presence of this file — a one-line sentinel the CI
workflow greps for — converts the `ci/benchmarks` PR gate from
**fail-on-threshold** to **warn-on-threshold** for the duration
of the dual-stack rewire window. See
[`.github/workflows/benchmarks.yml`](../../.github/workflows/benchmarks.yml)
`fail job on threshold trip` step for the gate branch and
[`docs/MID_REWIRE_HARDENING.md`](../MID_REWIRE_HARDENING.md) §3.3.1
for the policy rationale.

While this file exists:

- `capture-pr` still runs the iai-callgrind harness. Same
  instructions, same envelope, same artifact upload.
- `compare` still runs `scripts/bench/compare.py` against the
  rolling baseline and still posts the PR comment with the full
  delta table. Reviewers still see every number.
- `compare`'s return code is still surfaced as `has_fail=true`
  on the job output if the threshold trips, so
  `profile-on-fail` still runs and still uploads the samply
  profile artifact.
- The final `fail job on threshold trip` step — the only thing
  that would block merge — detects this sentinel and emits a
  GitHub `::warning::` annotation instead of exiting 1.

The warn path preserves every ounce of observability. What it
gives up is the merge-blocking signal, because during the
rewire window that signal would be structurally wrong: the
transitional state *is* expected to be slower than the post-2m
end state and faster than no-op, and gating against the pre-2k
baseline at the pre-2k threshold would either force the gate
off permanently (bad) or force the thresholds to relax
permanently (also bad). The warning-only mode is the "track
but don't gate" middle position.

## Why a sentinel file instead of a workflow `if:` flag

The sentinel lives in-tree, next to the baseline artifacts it
governs. That means:

- **Grep discoverability.** `rg MID_REWIRE_WARNING_WINDOW` from
  repo root finds this file, the workflow branch that consults
  it, and the §3.3.1 policy paragraph in a single pass. A
  workflow-only boolean or an Actions secret would be invisible
  from any `git grep` and would drift out of sync with the
  in-tree documentation.
- **Toggle = commit.** Opening and closing the window is a
  git commit authored by a human reviewer, with a commit
  message explaining *why* the window is open, *what* it's
  blanketing, and *which* future commit is expected to close
  it. An Actions-level toggle (repo-secret boolean, workflow
  input) has no commit trail.
- **Branch-dependent.** Different branches can legitimately be
  in different states: `feat/wallet-file-format` is in the
  rewire window; `dev` after 2m-cache lands is not; a hotfix
  branch forked off tagged-stable is not either. A sentinel
  file tracks this branch-by-branch naturally.
- **Auto-fails open on removal.** Deleting the file (the 2m-cache
  commit's job) immediately restores the merge-blocking gate on
  the next PR. No separate un-flip step, no risk of leaving the
  gate relaxed by accident.

## Closure criterion

Remove this file in the 2m-cache commit. That commit — or its
immediate follow-up — is also the right moment to rotate the
`bench-baseline` branch's `baseline.json` so that the first
post-window PR sees a fresh baseline captured from the
post-rewire code, not the pre-rewire code. See
[`docs/MID_REWIRE_HARDENING.md`](../MID_REWIRE_HARDENING.md)
§3.3.1 "Closing the window" for the exact rotation procedure.

If a non-rewire commit lands on this branch while the window
is open and *independently* regresses a benchmark, the PR
comment will still show the regression and the samply profile
will still be uploaded — just without the merge block. Review
the PR comment manually during review; don't merge a regression
without at least discussing it, even when the gate is warning-only.
